Domain: 
Dangers of the Australian sun.

Introduction:
Explore and visualise the potential health risks(heatstroke, skin cancer, etc.) that could be caused by the sunlight exposure in Australia. 

Data sources:

national uv exposure:
https://www.bom.gov.au/climate/maps/averages/uv-index/

uv exposure at different stations in Australia:
https://data.gov.au/data/organization/australian-radiation-protection-and-nuclear-safety-agency-arpansa

skin cancer data:
https://www.canceraustralia.gov.au/cancer-types/melanoma-skin/melanoma-skin-statistics

extreme weather hospitilisations:
https://www.aihw.gov.au/reports/injury/extreme-weather-injuries/data
